A ‚Üí B, ¬¨B, therefore ¬¨A.

Predicate Logic

Quantifiers:
‚àÄx, ‚àÉy.

Modal Logic

Possibility, necessity, counterfactual inference.

Paraconsistent Logic

Handling contradictions without collapse.
Used heavily in the Paradox Compass.

Temporal Logic

Before, after, eventually ‚Äî useful for causal and narrative modeling.

